The paper deals with improving the training of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for image classification and object recognition, which falls under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation techniques, which is a common topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed method involves mixing feature maps in a hidden layer, which is related to the Neural Networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing techniques, which is also related to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
